Niscomed NB-101 Nebulizer (White) Price: Rs.1575

Key Features

  • Piston Compressor
  • Operating Air Flow Rate at 8 L / min
  • Compressor Nebulizer
  • Lightweight
  • Easy Maintenance
  • Power Cord Storage
If your doctor has prescribed you with a nebulizer treatment then Niscomed NB-101 Nebulizer could help you regulate inhalation of medication in the comforts of your home. This compressor nebulizer is small and portable enabling you to experience a sound treatment wherever you go.

The Niscomed BN-101 nebulizer machine incorporates a compressor unit that supplies compressed air which is used to transform your liquid medication solution to fine vapor-like particles or aerosols. This medication in aerosol form can be easily inhaled by you through a mouthpiece.

Body

Ergonomically built to meet comfortable standards this nebulizer weighs about 1500 g making the operation easy and simple. The Niscomed compressor nebulizer device comprises of four main parts; the compressor unit air tube nebulization or medication cup and a mouthpiece. The compressor unit has an inbuilt piston which ensures strong pressure and smooth flow of the compressed air. The unit houses an on/off switch and a connector. The air tube is plugged into the connector linking the main unit to the medication cup and the mouthpiece.

Endowed with enhanced portability the Niscomed NB-101 nebulizer has an inbuilt holder that holds the air tube and the mouthpiece when not in use. The main unit also accommodates an extra storage compartment for the nebulizer parts thus preventing you from misplacing these parts. The convenient carry handle and the power cord storage come handy while travelling. This device is very easy to clean and maintain thus meeting hygienic standards. The angled mouthpiece allows you to inhale the medication with ease and comfort.

Performance and Features

The BN-101 nebulizer by Niscomed provides compressed air to the medication cup which flows at a rate of 8 l per min. This compressed air efficiently converts the medication solution into vapor-like particles or aerosols. The pressure exerted by the compressor unit ranges from 10 to 30 psi. The Niscomed nebulizer device operates at a temperature ranging from 10 to 40 degree Celsius. This device is powered by electricity and requires a power supply of 230 V 50 Hz.

column17:
Niscomed FPO-50 Pulse Oximeter Price: Rs.1560

Key Features

  • Fingertip Pulse Oximeter
  • LED Display
  • Low Battery Indicator

The Niscomed FPO-50 pulse oximeter has been immaculately engineered to effectively determine and read your pulse rate and oxygen percentage in your blood in the comforts of your own home. This Niscomed FPO-50 is a fingertip oximeter that needs to be clipped onto your fingers and preferably your index finger for the light sensors in the oximeter to quickly and precisely sense and measure the saturated oxygen in your blood.

Build

Built to enhance comfort and ease of use this Niscomed pulse oximeter is user-friendly and simple in its operation capable of delivering fast and easy spot-checks. This pulse oximeter is small and compact thereby allowing enhanced portability. Armed with a clear and easy-to-view LED screen this Niscomed pulse oximeter capably displays your pulse rates and blood saturated oxygen levels in BPM and SpO2 units respectively shown along a pleth waveform.

The LED display in the Niscomed FPO-50 pulse oximeter functions with enhanced efficacy as it is equipped with dual display colors and four-levels adjustable brightness features making it convenient for you. You can also view your readings comfortably as this pulse oximeter allows six modes of display directions enabling you to read your results in six different angles.

Performance

The Niscomed pulse oximter provides a safe and comfortable measuring procedure as this device utilizes a non-invasive method to procure your saturated oxygen readings or the amount of oxygen carried by the hemoglobin in your red blood cells. You simply have to place your fingers between the clip-ons in the device and press the button for your measurement process to function.

This pulse oximeter utilizes light-emitting diodes to detect the oxygen content in your blood. When you start the device it emits light which immediately passes through the sensors in your skin measuring the hemoglobin in your blood. Two types of lights comprising of red and infrared are emitted wherein the oxygenated blood absorbs the wavelength of the red light and the deoxygenated blood absorbs the wavelength of the infrared light.

While the oxygenated and deoxygenated blood absorb different light wavelengths the oximeter operates to find the ratio between the two and gives you the relative measurement therefore providing you an accurate estimate of your blood oxygen saturation.

Besides performing efficiently and delivering accurate results the Niscomed pulse oximeter also comes with convenient features that give you a comfortable user experience. The Auto shut-off feature in the Niscomed FPO-50 pulse oximeter enables the device to immediately shut down if left idle for more than 5 seconds therefore conserving energy and allowing safe usage. Moreover the display format is also saved when your device shuts down automatically preventing data loss.

For enhanced convenience this Pulse oximeter also displays your battery status and indicates when your battery is low. This Niscomed pulse oximeter requires 2 AAA batteries to function soundly.
